reviews: The pub was a bit cramped but it was a Sunday afternoon. The food was incredible and the barman was kind enough to give us a jug of hot water to warm my son's bottle. We wil definitely visit again.

We very much appreciate your feedback -- unfortunately, the pub does occasionally become quite busy just before the theatre begins. We hope you'll come back again soon, and perhaps will be lucky enough to be able to pick your favourite spot in the house :)

After walking around Kentish town on a cold winter's day, being able to have proper hearty meal in a cosy and warm atmosphere really put the Lion & Unicorn as one of the best pubs in North London. Had the 21day aged rump steak with seriously thick (and delicious) triple cooked chips and a reasonably priced bottle of Merlot to go with it. My wife had the Beetroot Risotto which was actually the surprise of the evening, earthy yet slightly sweet. If I'm in the area again, I'll 100% be dropping in!
What a lovely review Rory - very much like our risotto - Earthy but sweet!
Best triple cooked chips in a very long time
Best triple cooked chips in a very long time

We booked a table of 12 for our family Christmas get together at The Lion & Unicorn. The food was lovely and the staff were amazing, especially our host Danny. Thanks so much for making our night so magical!
Thank you very much for this amazing review, we are glad you enjoyed your Christmas Feast with us. Hope to see you again soon!

Got to enjoy a late breakfast here after stumbling across it by chance. Lovely relaxed atmosphere, 2 spacious outside areas (with heating!) And a lovely pub dog and owner to welcome you. Attentive quick service.
Away from the bustle of the high street I could've been sat in the countryside for all I knew.
Loud woof woof from Eddie (meaning a big thanks!) We appreciate your lovely review and 5 *'s rating Eden, thank you. Can't wait to see you again soon :)
Large pub with several outdoor seating areas, including one with a retractable roof. Friendly service. Good quality and value food.
Thank you very much for your kind words Helen, much appreciated. We hope you will come back here soon again.
Had a really good Sunday lunch here. It's very much a "food pub", although it didn't seem "way gastro" to me and it looks like it welcomes people dropping in for a pint.

Yay! We're so happy you had an amazing time with us, we do hope to see you soon! It's Valentine'y today and we have a fabulous V-day specials menu, so if you have nothing planned, please do give us a visit!

Regards,
Lion & Unicorn Team
Really lovely, cozy pub with fabulous menu and friendly staff. The menu, in particular the hake and pear crumble was excellent. The biscuits baked on site are amazing. Will definitely be back!
Thank you for your wonderful review, we hope to see you real soon!

Delicious Sunday roast. The place is fairly large with indoor and outdoor seating so always plenty of room, although it does get very busy.

Facilities
- Dog & kid friendly (kids get pens & drawing toys, spare sunscreen if needed!, bowls for dogs)
- retractable outdoor roof so rain friendly
- outdoor seating at both front & back of venue
- heaters & blankets
- can accommodate large tables e.g. 10 people

Service was really welcoming and friendly, but just a tad slow, however they were at max capacity so don't blame them!
We ordered the roast beef & chicken with a side of pigs in blankets & cauliflower cheese. The portions are substantial so you certainly won't be hungry! The Yorkshire and vegetables were fantastic (buttered cabbage, swede mash, carrots), as was the cauliflower cheese.
We got extra gravy & horseradish to go with our dishes as well.

I prefer crispy roast potatoes so only had one (although they were nice) & beef was well done, but these are really minor items.
Toilets were a bit unpleasant.

Overall, a great venue for food with friends or family, definitely look forward to going again!

Thank you very much for the detailed review!
It's a shame that the toilets werent up to scratch on this occasion, we will have to make more regulatr checks to keep it up to our regualr high standards. See you again soon :)
Nice pub. Good beer. Didn't eat here but menu looked great.

Don’t underestimate this little local pub: with a real fireplace roaring in the winter. Very friendly, welcoming and accommodating staff, Including at lunch hour, outdoor seating under heaters. And TO DIE FOR Lunch fried chicken burger, reminds me of American southern fried chicken- actually melts in your mouth but has the crunch. I wish they’d put it on the dinner menu.. I’d have it more often. Id post a photo but it’s too late…
Ahh Tessa, thanks so much for your lovely words - as a just reward please feel free to order the LFC burger at whatever time of day you like 😄
Warm and cosy pub with friendly staff, amazing food and two super hosts Phil & Eddie! Thank you for your hospitality!
Ah Luigi, thanks so much for your review! Eddie was very sad not to reciee any of your chicken! He'll still be here next time though to chance his paw!

I am visiting from America for my birthday and I must that this establishment is the best pub that I have had the pleasure of experiencing!! The staff and owner were exceptionally welcoming and kind. The atmosphere and food were AMAZING !!! I walked in through the doors and I absolutely fell in LOVE 😍 I wish I could stay here forever!!! Thank you Phil for the best old fashioned I’ve ever had and A MILLION THANKS YOU’s for Jackie Oh! 😉😘 I will definitely be back my next visit to the UK 🇬🇧 !!
Aaaaaw you are amazing yourself! Hope you'll be back soon, can't wait to see you again! Have a safe flight back home!

I came here for a birthday celebration and I was greeted by a lovely waitress! The service from start to finish was speedy and attentive especially from Jamie who was only working her first shift! Anna also looked after us and made my night! The bartender had great recommendations of drinks! Thank you to everyone and I will definitely be returning!!

It was great having you here and celebrating your birthday <3 Looking forward to seeing you again soon, you will be hugged well by Jaime ... and ME of course! Many thanks for your review. Best, Anna x

This pub is amazing, a hidden Gem!
we’ve had family occasions here, Sunday lunches and just drinks in the lovely Garden. Every time we’ve been, the staff are amazing, kind and so accommodating.  The food is also lovely!
No Charlotte - YOU are the hidden gem! Thanks so much for your review
Lovely pub. Chilled atmosphere and lovely food. Highly recommended.
Thank you very much for your 5 stars rating and kind words Simon. We are pleased you enjoyed youf food and vibes here. Hope to see you again soon!

The Lion and Unicorn is the perfect neighbourhood pub. I love the food and the service is excellent. The decoration makes it feel so cosy and inviting. They also offer lovely wines and drinks. Nice pub for family meals but to meet up with friends too.

Thanks Sophia, we're glad you enjoy coming in our pub! We can't wait for your next visit. See you soon!

Regards,
Lion & Unicorn Team

I'm in London for a week, solo and found this place about 10 mins walk from my accommodation. I was able to have an alcohol free beer (I don't drink) and work with my laptop for an hour or so, then had the fish and chips followed by the cheesecake and coffee, all were excellent and a great way to spend a rare quiet evening whilst away from home. Friendly staff and cute dog too ☺️
Thanks so much for your review David! Glad you enjoyed your evening with us, even if you were working! Hope to see you next time in town
London prices. Enormous portions. I visited on a Sunday so plenty of choice for their traditional lunch. HUGE! You must have a good appetite for their lunch. Staff exceptional. Excellent
Thank you again for taking the time to let us know how we did. We hope you have a great day!
Such a lovely place to go and have a drink or some lunch... the staff are very good and friendly as the manager.  Everytime i go I have a great time with such a lovely atmosphere...
Ah thanks Juan, we love haing you everytime
Lovely pub, friendly staff, dog friendly and the vegan burger and fries was great, very tasty! Yes, all a bit pricey but then what isn't these days. Treat yourself when you can!
Celeste, we're glad you had such a wonderful experience with us!
Beautiful pub with welcoming staff and a roaring fire. Will try the restaurant and theatre next time!
Thank you for your wonderful review! We hope to see you soon!

Had Sunday lunch here at the suggestion of my son who lives locally. Pleasant airy pub in a quiet leafy burb road. Chilled atmosphere. (Sunday lunch out can be stressful in Suffolk...). I had the lamb rump, which is not actually that easy to cook. Flavour was sublime, and the texture was fine. My wife had the beef (she is the daughter of a Somerset beef farmer so it's all about beef. ) She couldn't fault it. Lots of thoughtfully prepared vegetables: the red cabbage was flavoursome, the parsnip maybe nearing the end of its season. Huge delicious Yorkshires. My son ordered the wine and chose an ambrosial CNDP. I usually avoid French wine but this was the goods. The front garden was lovely. Tobacco is always an unpleasant distraction, but to be fair, not everyone was smoking tobacco. All in all a very enjoyable Sunday lunch.
Thanks for such a in depth review, so glad you had a lovely time. Our rear garden is totally non-smoking for future reference
Once again food was amazing! Steak tartar and the venison was absolutely fantastic! Great atmosphere and great pub!!
Many thanks for your review Anne, can't wait to have you back here soon

The food here is excellent  best roast i have had in a long time.very tasty. The pub is lovely and the service is fantastic. Will definitely being booking again. Thank you Lion and unicorn
.
We appreciate your positive review about your recent experience with us!

I suggest the landlord Phil is got rid of, I have spent over £1000 in there over the past month! Only to be ignored! If this is not sorted and discussed with me and Youngs the brewery I will take the ignorance of the landlord as extremely rude!
You will notice a loss in guests as time goes on as we know many people in the local area!
His dog Eddie pesters you whilst eating, which is a right put off as soon as eating food! Anaemic sausages, pale chips that are supposed to be TRIPLE cooked and such poor service that I take the glasses plates…etc myself just to help out! I was a very valuable customer as I recently had a substantial win on Euros and your employees don’t even know that! I suggest you have a serious word with Phil as he was extremely rude!! whilst on the till screen, I asked a question, and was just ignored, he admitted he was not listening to me as I asked him about your top shelf drinks (which are extremely overpriced) Maybe he is on a bad comedown after Glastonbury, but no need to take it out on unknown valuable customers and you will see a loss, I promise that.
Kind regards, your customer of the month, but not any more!
Enjoy struggling with the extremely rude Landlords! I would give St John’s prison in Antigua more stars than you deserve
Many thanks for taking the time to review us Gavin.

First time visit, but definitely not last! We were sitting in the back garden, which was in a great sun spot. The food we ordered was generous portions - I had the Brie sandwich and my partner had the fish fingers bap, all really tasty! All staff were super friendly and attentive, but obviously very busy as it was a sunny Saturday, so I’d recommend ordering from the app (:
Thanks Gergana! Hope to see you again soon

We had an amazing Sunday roast in the garden under the sun today. The 12-hour slow roasted lamb shoulder, accompanied with pigs-in-blankets and cauliflower cheese (plenty for four to share), was simply delicious. Thank you to Danica and her colleagues for a wonderful welcome and service!
Thank you very much for your lovely rewiev. Hope to see you again soon!
Local pub full of charms, very calm and perfect for family catch-up. Good food choice, a bit pricy maybe but you enjoy your time. Bonus points : no music or TV ! :D
Delicious as always. Amazing staff, incredible food, welcoming and warm ambience - a home from home. Thanks to all the staff for your hard work and making it such a joy to visit!
Hannah, we strive for 100% satisfaction, and it is great to see you had such a positive experience at The Lion & Unicorn.

Gave us a great 90th birthday for my grandparents, they love it at the Lion and unicorn and they had such a great afternoon. Thanks to all the staff and the GM how put the effort in. Dave and Joan love you guys!

Oh what an honour and pleasure it was to celebrate this special day with you guys! Even Sun was shining specialy for you ;) We always are really happy to see your faces, please pass our kindest regards to all family and friends. Can't wait to see you again soon! Loads of love, Lions and Unicorns :)
